# ovh_vps_disk (Data Source)

Use this data source to retrieve information about a specific disk attached to a VPS.

## Example Usage

{{tffile "examples/data-sources/vps_disk/example_1.tf"}}

## Argument Reference

* `service_name` - (Required) The internal name of the VPS (e.g.
  `vps-XXXXXX.vps.ovh.net`).
* `disk_id` - (Required) Numeric identifier of the disk attached to the VPS.

## Attributes Reference

The following attributes are exported:

* `id` - `service_name|disk_id` composite identifier.
* `type` - Disk type (`primary` or `additional`).
* `state` - Disk state (`connected`, `disconnected`, `pending`).
* `size` - Disk size in GiB.
* `bandwidth_limit` - Disk bandwidth limit.
* `monitoring` - Whether OVHcloud monitoring is enabled on the disk.
* `low_free_space_threshold` - Threshold (in MiB) below which a low-free-space
  alert is raised.
